---

## What Went Well

1. **Clean product spec** — SPEC.md was detailed and actionable
2. **Clear tech stack** — Next.js 14 + TypeScript + Recharts + YouTube OAuth was the right call
3. **YouTube API integration** — OAuth flow and API proxy working
4. **Production-ready testing** — Playwright tests passing
5. **Docker setup** — Production deployment streamlined
6. **Analytics infrastructure** — `lib/adoption.ts` + API routes deployed for tracking OAuth connections

---

## Adoption Analytics — IMPLEMENTED ✅

| Component | Path | Status |
|-----------|------|--------|
| Analytics library | `lib/adoption.ts` | ✅ Live |
| Record connection (POST) | `app/api/analytics/connect/route.ts` | ✅ Live |
| Get adoption data (GET) | `app/api/analytics/adoption/route.ts` | ✅ Live |
| OAuth callback integration | `app/api/youtube/auth/callback/route.ts` | ✅ Fires on OAuth success |
| Dashboard widget | `components/AdoptionDashboard.tsx` | ✅ Built |

**Production note:** In-memory tracker resets on server restart. For persistent analytics, integrate PostHog or a proper KV store (Redis/Upstash).

**Next step:** Connect PostHog or set up persistent tracking before scaling distribution.

---

## What Needs Attention

### Missing from Launch
- **Launch content posted?** — CMO to verify Day 1–5 content was actually published (Twitter, Reddit)
- **Early user feedback loop** — No explicit beta feedback collection documented

### Technical Debt
- Rate limiting on YouTube API (10k units/day) — caching implemented but needs load testing
- No email capture / waitlist for overflow
- No dark mode (marked out of scope)
- In-memory analytics resets on restart — needs PostHog/Upstash upgrade for production

---

